Package uk.ac.rhul.cs2800

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Calculator
    Allows for the calculation of String expressions.
    OperatorType
    This interface is used alongside the operator Factory which will be used to calculate the expression on the operator specifed by the factory.
    Runnable
    This is a functional interface which is used to notify observers in the CalcController class to execute a method.
    ViewInterface
    An interface to be using to add observers to a controller when used with User Interfaces.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    AsciiView
    This is a text based interface which is automatically used if the program is started from the command line.
    CalcController
    This is a Controller which creates a view and a model.
    CalcModel
    This is an overall model of the calculator which evaluates expressions of infix and postfix.
    DivideOperation
    This class is a part of a factory design pattern which is used to Divide two operands.
    Driver
    Runs the Model Assembly of the calculator using a User Interface.
    Entry
    This class represents the values stored in a stack.
    MinusOperation
    This class is a part of a factory design pattern which is used to subtract one operand from another.
    MultiplyOperation
    This class is a part of a factory design pattern which is used to Multiply two operands together.
    NumStack
    A facade providing a simplified stack of numeric values.
    OperatorFactory
    A factory which is used to generate the correct operator calculation.
    OpStack
    A facade providing a simplified stack of Symbol values.
    PlusOperation
    This class is a part of a factory design pattern which is used to add two operands.
    RevPolishCalc
    Evaluate Reverse Polish String expressions.
    Stack
    This class represents a stack of Entry values.
    StandardCalc
    Evaluates infix string expressions.
    StrStack
    A facade providing a simplified stack of Strings.
